dataIdInfo.idAbs: This data set defines the best known outter extents of IDNR property. Most boundary polygons represent IDNR ownership; some polygons however, represent areas that are owned by federal agencies or private interests that are currently being managed by IDNR resources.
dataIdInfo.idPurp: Outter boundary of all recreation and conservation sites owned or managed by the Illinois Department of Natural Resources. This layer of boundary polygons consists of best known estimates of where property the is owned and managed by IDNR is spatically located.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: This layer is a collaborative effort involving long-term committment from personal of the Illinois Department of Natural Resources and the Illinois Natural History Survey.

LegConsts.useLimit: See access and use constraints information.

Consts.useLimit: “IDNR is not responsible for any undesirable results or decisions made from these property data. These data should only be used for approximating property parcel locations. IDNR is not responsible or liable for any accidents or injuries sustained by users of data while travelling to property. Data users are responsible for using due care in abiding by posted signage on and near the property. These property data were created for internal management use, and should not be used to support legal claims. Any errors found in property data should be reported to IDNR for correction. Please contact Charles Foor at IDNR, 217-782-3073 or charlie.foor@illinois.gov to report errors.”
